This location is great as far as I'm concerned because it gives you the luxury of being away from all the chaos and crowds when your done exploring the attractions.	If you’re looking for posh elegance, or five-star amenities, and a snobby staff, then the Murray Hill is NOT for you.	I agree that this accommodation can not be compared with a big five star fancy new hotel, and the furniture is from the eighties, but the price is very reasonable and I find the suites extremely comfortable.	It doesn't count as luxury, but neither does my house, and we would stay there again any time.